In his Christmas message, President Biden reflects on the stillness and universal message of the Christmas story. He acknowledges the challenges of the past few years, including the pandemic and political division, but highlights the progress and resilience of the American people. He calls for unity and compassion, urging people to see each other as fellow Americans deserving of respect. The President shares his personal experience of loss during the holiday season and emphasizes the importance of kindness and reaching out to those in need. He also pays tribute to the men and women serving in the military and ends with a message of hope and light for the future.